**Full ReBAC Content:**
ReBAC grants access based on entity relationships in a graph, enabling fine-grained, dynamic authz. Differs from RBAC (roles) and ABAC (attributes) by focusing on traversable connections.
**Core Concepts:** Entities (users/resources), Relationships (edges: parent-child, member, owner), Policies (relation-based rules), Graph DB for traversal.
**Prior Knowledge:** RBAC: User → Role → Permission. ABAC: Attributes match policies. ReBAC builds with relations (e.g., user member_of team → team owner doc → user accesses doc).
**Common Models/Use Cases:**
- Google Zanzibar: Relation tuples (doc#edit@team), computed via unions/exclusions; powers Drive/YouTube.
- Parent-Child: Hierarchical (org → dept → employee; access propagates via traversal).
- Social Networks: Friends/followers graphs.
- SaaS: Multi-tenant workspaces/projects/docs.
